dct_description_sm: United States Coast and Geodetic Survey.
Relief shown by contours and spot heights; depths shown by soundings and isolines.

"Triangulation by G. Davidson, E.O.C. Ord, U.S.A., W.E. Greenwell, A.W. Chase, D.B. Wainwright, and A.F. Rodgers, Assistants ... topography by A.W. Chase and W.M. Johnson, Assistants ... hydrography by Lieut. E.H.C. Leutze, Lieut. Comdr. H.C. Taylor, U.S.N., and G. Davidson, Assistants ... astronomical observations by G. Davidson, Assistant ... magnetic observations by W.P. Trowbridge, U.S.A., and H.E. Nichols, U.S.N. Assistants ..."
Oriented with north toward upper right.
Inset map: San Pedro Harbor. Scale 1:10,000.
